This large park surrounded by residential buildings is decorated with trees and flower beds. It has play areas for children. Created as part of a real estate program, on the former site of the Ministries of Transport, Equipment and Housing, this garden is best known to residents of the neighborhood. It is organized around a vast lawn surrounded by prunus, apple and decorative pear trees. In summer, wisteria and clematis transform the 12 pergolas of the flowered arches avenue which leads to a gazebo. Punctuated with cypresses, a beautiful, flowery Mediterranean garden invites you to get away from it all. Children can enjoy a 200 m2 play area. This park is one of the first gardens in the City of Paris to be labeled as an ecological green space.

Beautiful park in the middle of residential buildings. You can definitely rest well here on warm days. Not a tourism magnet... Good thing. A beautifully planted piece of greenery in the middle of the city.
